notesStmt.note: Title from title statement (f. 1r): Īn kitāb dar ṭibb az nuskhahā-yi hinduyān taṣnīf Shaykh Tahir.
Item is not dated, likely copied in the late 17th to 18th century.
Catalog entry, 744, pasted onto front inside cover.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Copy of a book on medicine in 49 chapters. Text composed in 1066 A.H. (1656 CE) (f. 2r).

supportDesc.extent: 189 leaves : 200 x 140 (135 x 90) mm bound to 200 x 155 mm

collation.p: Paper, 189 + i; 1-19⁸ 20⁶ 21¹⁰ 22⁶ 23¹⁰ 24⁶ [i]; [1], 2-74, 79-127, 129-147, 147-153, 155-164, 166-171, 171-178, 189, 180-194, foliation in ink, upper right verso, carelessly done in terms of skipping numbers, repeating numbers, and turning the leaves while the foliation was still wet.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 11-13 long lines; catchwords every verso, lower left.

binding.p: Reddish leather over pasteboard (Type III); blind stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis (bookplate inside front cover).
